&ldquo;Democracy is the worst form of government, except for all the others.&rdquo;
  ― Winston S. Churchill
 In the current world political climate, it seems that in many instances democracy and the related values (equality, human rights, and so on) are increasingly taking a back seat to populism and increasingly authoritarian leaderships. One sometimes has to consider whether authoritarian states would in fact be more effective in this day and age.
